balanceOf(address).details: Gets the balance of the specified address.

params.owner: The address to query the balance of.

returns._0: uint256 representing the amount owned by the passed address.

balanceOfStage(uint256,address).details: Gets the balance of the specified address at a certain stage.

params.owner: The address to query the balance of.

returns._0: uint256 representing the amount owned by the passed address.

buyTokens(address).details: low level token purchase ***DO NOT OVERRIDE*** This function has a non-reentrancy guard, so it shouldn't be called by another `nonReentrant` function.

params.rateFirst: Share of unlocking at this stage.
params.rateSecond: Share of unlocking at this stage.

params.cap: The maximum number of tokens available for sale at this stage.

getCalendar(uint256).details: Gets the calendar certain stage data.

returns._0: (uint256 time, uint256[2]) Stage start time and rates

getCurrentStage().details: Gets the current crowdsale stage identifier

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}.     * To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

getRoleMember(bytes32,uint256).details: Returns one of the accounts that have `role`. `index` must be a value between 0 and {getRoleMemberCount}, non-inclusive.     * Role bearers are not sorted in any particular way, and their ordering may change at any point.     * WARNING: When using {getRoleMember} and {getRoleMemberCount}, make sure you perform all queries on the same block. See the following https://forum.openzeppelin.com/t/iterating-over-elements-on-enumerableset-in-openzeppelin-contracts/2296[forum post] for more information.

getRoleMemberCount(bytes32).details: Returns the number of accounts that have `role`. Can be used together with {getRoleMember} to enumerate all bearers of a role.

getStage(uint256).details: Gets the stage data by identifier

returns._0: (uint256, uint256, uint256) total supply, stage cap & stage rate

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`.     * If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event.     * Requirements:     * - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

pause().details: Called by a pauser to pause, triggers stopped state.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

releasableAmount(address).details: Calculates the amount that has already vested but hasn't been released yet.

releasedOf(address).details: Gets the released token amount of the specified address.

params.owner: The address to query the release of.

returns._0: uint256 representing the amount released by the passed address.

releasedOfStage(uint256,address).details: Gets the release of the specified address at a certain stage.

params.owner: The address to query the release of.

returns._0: uint256 representing the amount released by the passed address.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner.     * NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account.     * Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced).     * If the calling account had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event.     * Requirements:     * - the caller must be `account`.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`.     * If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event.     * Requirements:     * - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

params.value: Locked by vesting period if true

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

transferTokens(address,uint256).details: Transfer token for a specified addresses.

unpause().details: Called by a pauser to unpause, returns to normal state.

vested().details: Returns true if the contract is lock by vesting logic, and false otherwise.
